SHEEP POX IN ISRAEL
(Date of previous outbreak of sheep pox in Israel reported to the OIE: Oct
2001).
Extract from the monthly report of Israel for December 2002, received from
Dr Oded Nir, Director of Veterinary and Animal Health Services, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan:
Location: Bet-Yehoshua, Hasharon district
No. of outbreaks in December 2002: 1
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
ovi / 574 / 32 / 4 / 0 / 0
---
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Sheep pox is rather endemic in Israel; during the years 1997-2001,4,6,12,9
and 17 outbreaks (respectively) have been reported to the OIE. Only sheep
are affected, even in flocks that include both sheep and goats. Mass annual
vaccinations, in sheep only, are practised. The live attenuated vaccine in
use is locally produced (sheep-pox RM 65 strain). - Mod.AS].
See Also
1997
